model.checker_program:
import json
from sys import stdin

def check_inputs (inputs, outputs):
    scores=[]
    lis = [ 0 for i in range( len( inputs ) ) ]
    iterate = -1

    for inps, outps in zip(inputs, outputs):
        iterate += 1
        inps = inps.strip()
        outps = outps.strip()
        ok = 1

        if  len(inps.split()) != len(outps.split()):
            ok = 0
        for inp, outp in zip(inps.split(), outps.split()):
            if abs(float(inp) - float(outp)) > 1e-3:
                ok = 0
        if ok:
            scores.append(1)
            lis[iterate] = 1
        else:
            scores.append(0)
            lis[iterate] = 0

    return scores,lis

def process(data):
    # Whatever you do, I am not giving any marks!
    scores,b = check_inputs(data["expected_outputs"], data["outputs"])
    score = sum(scores)*1.0/len(scores)
    return score, b

if __name__ ==  '__main__':
    stdin = stdin.read().split('\n')

    # Get the run directory for the submission we need to evaluate.
    run_directory = stdin[-1]

    # request.json contains the data submitted for the current.
    request = json.load(open(run_directory + "request.json"))

    data = {
        # The submitted source code
        "source": request["source"],
        # The list of test cases
        "testcases": request["testcase_sources"],
        # The submitted language key (Eg: 5 for python)
        "lang": request["lang"],
        # I'll tell you how to fill this next
        "expected_outputs": request["expected_outputs"],
        "outputs": [],
    }

    for index in range(len(request["testcase_sources"])):
        output = open(run_directory + "output%05d.out" %(index)).read()
        data["outputs"].append(output)

    # Gathered all the data we could, lets process it
    score, testcase_status = process(data)

    print score #print overall score?*
    print " ".join(str(i) for i in testcase_status) #print if each test case passed

101 Hack is back! HackerRank will be hosting 101 Hack on the last saturday of every month at 17:00 UTC, starting this month. Now, you know for sure what to look forward to last saturday of every month!

It's all about speed, accuracy and efficiency. Inside the contest are 3 challenges. You have exactly 180 minutes to solve them. Every second counts.

HackerRank invites you to join the contest to compete against hackers from across the globe.

Next up is 20/20 Hack on July 6th


Sign up at www.hackerrank.com/2020hack
